 for these young men to grow up gay in an immigrant family, to be the one gay person in their school and ethnic community, and to be a person of color in predominantly White gay spaces. Brown and Gay in LA is an homage to second-generation gay men and their radical redefinition of what it means to be gay, to be a man, to be a person of color, and, ultimately, what it means to be an American.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aAsian American gayszCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial conditions. 0aGay menzCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aAcceptance.  aAsian American.  aBody.  aBullying.  aChildhood.  aClass.  aCollege.  aComing out.  aCommunity.  aCovering.  aCultural Centers.  aEducation.  aEthnicity.  aFamily.  aFilipino.  aGay.  aGayborhoods.  aGender.  aHigher Education.  aImmigration.  aIntersectionality.  aLGBTQ.  aLatino.  aMasculinity.  aQueer.  aRace.  aRacism.  aReligion.  aRespectability.  aSexualities.  aSexuality.  aSizeism.  aSocial Media.  aStudent Organizations.  aTherapy.  aTransgender.  aTransnational.  aUrban.  aWhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075162840uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479806614.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479806614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479806614/original  a978-3-11-075162-8  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK